Subject: RE: [VB] Fuel pumps

From time to time I will make forays into the local wrecking yards and
pick up a rotary fuel pump off of some small foreign car. A lot of these
are frame mount and can be had for under $20. Add a fuel pressure
regulator and you're in. I'm always looking for little doodads to use
here and there. Always playing with different carburetors too.

67 Single Cab, DP 1641cc 34 PICT-3 (Thumper)
71 Trike 1776cc Dual T-4 34 PDSIT-3
VolksAir 1585cc 31 PICT
http://mywebpage.netscape.com/alphahr/case.html
Ray, Kent WA
